programme.title: Jane Eyre

programme.title: Jane Eyre

programme.title: Jane Eyre
programme.desc: Having left Thornfield, a heartbroken Jane finds herself alone, penniless and starving on the moors. Jane begins a new life as a teacher, but when Rivers proposes marriage she thinks she hears Rochester call out her name and knows she must go back to Thornfield.

programme.title: The Great British Bake Off
programme.desc: One of the most popular television programmes in the United Kingdom returns for an eighth season as twelve new budding bakers compete to be crowned the champion. programme.title: Jamies Family Christmas
programme.sub-title: Breakfast, Brunches and All the Bits in Between

programme.title: The Hairy Bikers Twelve Days of Christmas

programme.title: Holiday Baking Championship

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: This years competition has been the most fiercely fought yet, with more top chefs from across the country than ever, all battling it out in the kitchen to cook at the fabulous Peoples Banquet. The winners have been announced and this special documentary follows the successful chefs in the run up to the banquet, as they make the painstaking preparations, for what is one of the most important meals they will ever cook.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The spotlight is on Scotland. Returning contenders Michael Smith, Tony Singh and Mark Greenaway are all determined to get one of their dishes to the banquet. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Returning contenders Michael Smith, Tony Singh and Mark Greenaway cook their fish dishes. Will a traditional Scottish soup, a chowder or a risky no-cook mackerel dish impress veteran judge Angela Hartnett MBE?

programme.desc: The competition heats up as the three returning Scottish contenders, Michael Smith, Tony Singh and Mark Greenaway, cook their main courses. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Scottish returning contenders Michael Smith, Tony Singh and Mark Greenaway have just one more chance to impress veteran judge Angela Hartnett MBE and win their place in front of the judges. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Only one chef can make it through to the national finals to represent Scotland and cook at a special banquet at the Royal Albert Hall.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The curtain raises on the competition in the North West. How will Aiden Byrnes dish entitled `Mad as a Box of Frogs go down with veteran Phil Howard? Will he trounce Mary-Ellen McTagues crab starter or will Chris Hollands `Oriental style beef broth with a twis score more highly with Phil?

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The North West chefs cook their fish courses. Will Aiden Byrnes `The Culinary Joke - a take on a classic prawn cocktail - raise a laugh, or will Mary-Ellen McTagues dish of dover sole or Chris Hollands `Gone Fishing salmon dish prove winners?

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs cook their main course. Will Aiden Byrnes witty beef dish entitled `Long Horn Beef with Noodle Pot prove a winner, or will Mary-Ellen McTagues goat dish called `Our Kid raise a smile? Perhaps Chris Holland will score highly with his dish called `A Tasting of Pork.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Its the chefs last chance to impress before the final two are chosen to face the `Great British Menu judging panel. Which dessert will help get them through? programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Its decision time for the chefs from the North West. One chef has already left the competition and only two remain. The judges are joined by celebrity guest judge writer, presenter and performer Rowland Rivron.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: In central England, three culinary heavyweights return to the `Great British Menu kitchen. Two Michelin star chef Daniel Clifford creates a dish called `A Trip to the Chippy, where nothing is as it first appears. That is also the theme for Michelin star chef Richard Bainbridges starter, `banana split, while Will Holland offers up goats cheese mousse, balsamic jelly and gingerbread.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Here, the chefs try to impress with their fish courses. Daniel Clifford puts up a creative dish called `Catch of the Day. Will judge Marcus Wareing find the comedy value in Will Hollands coconut poached brill, crab, celeriac and tomato essence?

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs in central England cook their main courses. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The chefs in central England have one last chance to impress Marcus Wareing before the final two are chosen to face the judging panel. Will Daniel Cliffords `Going Out with a Bang be good enough? Has Richard Bainbridge dropped the comedy ball with his coffee and chocolate dessert called `Time to Reflect? programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Its decision time for the chefs from the central England region. Only two chefs remain to cook their entire menus for judges Prue Leith, Matthew Fort and Oliver Peyton. The panel is joined by guest judge, comedian and actor Jim Moir, known to millions as Vic Reeves.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The South West chefs battle it out for a chance to cook at the special banquet. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The South West chefs cook their fish courses here. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The South West chefs cook their main courses and veteran Tom Kerridge is looking for perfection. Will Chris Edens spin on a fast food classic simply called `B.L.T gain top points? programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: For the South West chefs, which dessert will progress? Peach melba, apple pie and `Lolly and Sweets fight it out.

programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: Its decision time for the chefs from the South West and only two remain. programme.title: Great British Menu
programme.desc: The Welsh chefs raise the curtain with their starters, but which one is going to produce a showstopper?
